Is it any harder than this?<p><pre><code>    class Team {
        List<Player> players = new List<Player>();
        public void AddPlayer(Player player) {
            // rule checks here
            players.add(player);
        }
        public IEnumerable<Player> Players {
            get { return players; }
        }
    }
</code></pre>
Covers SOLID, DDD, the lot.<p>One should never inherit the list. Encapsulate perhaps but the list is there as a fundamental structure and to inherit from it would break the encapsulation of the domain model you are constructing and increase efferent coupling.
